column5: Hi, Someone can help me? I'm looking a fishing store in Toronto...I live in est area...close my home there is canadian tire but I am not satisfed of fishing staff that it has... Let me know Riccardo

where do you live in east of toronto there is pro js warden and sheppard there are two other fishing stores near midland and sheppard and markam and sheppard as well as tight lines on brock rd just south of 401 in pickering all sell live bait as well
JB's Fishing Depot, Ronson Dr. North side of the 401 between Martin Grove and Kipling.
Theres a bass pro in Vaughn been there seem to have good selection
If you're looking for fly gear, there's Wilson's Fly Fishing at Queen and Sherbourne. Otherwise, you're looking forward to traffic...
He lives in Toronto, he is used to it.   :angry:
I would definitely second JB's and Wilsons.
JB's is a candy store. I'll say no more
LeBaron's is close to eastern Toronto at Woodbine and #7.
